==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[columba]]'', a "[[dove]]"

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Columba'''

# [[w:Columba|St. Columba of Iona]] (Old Irish ''Columb Cille'', meaning "Dove of the church"); one of the [[Gaelic]] [[missionary]] [[monk]]s who reintroduced [[Christianity]] to [[Scotland]] during the [[Dark Ages]].
# Any of three other Christian [[saint]]s who bore the name Columba.
#{{constellation}}: A small [[winter]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to resemble a [[dove]]. It was introduced by Augustin Royer in 1679, as a split from the constellation [[Canis Major]].

